Different models capture different signals:

LSTM / sequence nets → complex temporal patterns, volatility clusters, non-linear dependencies.

Prophet / NeuralProphet → interpretable trend + seasonality + holidays/regime effects.

Tree models (XGBoost/LightGBM / RF) → integrate many engineered features (fundamentals, technical indicators, macro features) and handle non-linear interactions.

Statistical models (ARIMA/ETS) → capture simple autoregressive structure and give well-calibrated baselines.

Robustness: markets change regime — ensembles reduce model risk and overfitting to one pattern.

Horizon specificity: a model that’s best for 3-month jumps may be suboptimal for 60-month CAGR — ensemble lets you specialize per horizon.

Uncertainty & calibration: combining outputs enables quantile/CI estimation and better risk signals (helpful for HHS & advisory language).

