LSTM (PyTorch or TF) — sequence window input (30–180 days) → predict horizon return.

Prophet or NeuralProphet — capture seasonality + trend.

XGBoost / LightGBM — features + lagged returns.

RandomForest — alternative tree baseline.

Simple statistical model (ARIMA / ETS) — baseline.

Linear Regression — very fast baseline (keep for sanity checks).

Ensembling strategies

Validation-based weighted average: compute rolling-window validation performance for each model/horizon/ticker-group and set weights proportional to recent performance (decayed weights).

Stacking (meta-learner): use out-of-fold predictions from base models to train a simple meta-learner (Ridge or XGBoost) that outputs final prediction.

Per-horizon & per-ticker group selection: for illiquid or special tickers, prefer tree models + fundamentals; for very liquid series, LSTM + ARIMA may win.

Uncertainty: produce quantiles via:

quantile regression models (LightGBM quantile) OR

empirical distribution from multiple models + historical residuals.

